cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper presents a neural network for predicting purchasing intent in an Ecommerce setting, which involves modeling varied, semi-structured input data comprising categoricals, quantities, and unique instances. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). However, given that the paper focuses on automatic feature learning using recurrent neural networks, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also possible because the paper involves natural language processing and data security.
